Author: theedm09ka
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 21/09/18  I’m writing to you this week from Singapore, where I have had some incredible experiences, speaking with people about the latest phase in our mission to bridge the gap between traditional finance and the emerging blockchain industry. In my last FORTnightly message I touched upon the emergence of security tokens. We see this as the next evolutionary step for our industry; establishing more products, markets and opportunities for broader participation and adoption. I've previously shared the work we have been doing behind the scenes at the GSX Group towards this goal, and I am excited to let you know about our latest endeavours.  1. My Trip to Asia and The GSP Protocol  The meetings and events during my time in Singapore have been focused on communicating our technology solution, which we believe is required to support tokenised securities through good governance, best practices and the highest regulatory standards. We have called the solution the Global Securities Protocol (GSP).   We aim to use the GSP to transform capital markets with blockchain technology, bringing together other stock exchanges, investment banks and qualified institutions to utilise the GSP, creating more avenues for issuers to gain access to the blockchain powered finance of tokenised securities. Naturally, RKT will play a pivotal role in the GSP, which will have public access and transparency. A protocol designed specifically for tokenised securities, open to all. More detailed information will be announced shortly.  2. Atlantic NeoTechnologies joins the Sponsor Firm Network  Please join me in welcoming our latest Sponsor Firm, Atlantic NeoTechnologies (ANT), to our incredible community of token advisory experts. ANT is part of a Group with extensive experience in international banking, investment advice and asset management. You can read more about ANT's approval status as a Sponsor Firm here:  https://gbx.gi/news/atlantic-neotechnologies-joins-the-sponsor-firm-network/?utm_source=telegram&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=ceomessage   3. Sponsor Summit: Singapore  As part of GBX’s commitment to our Sponsor Firms,  we maintain a continuous two-way relationship, open to dialogue and feedback. Holding Sponsor Summits is a great way to bring our community of Sponsor Firms together, and provide a platform for discussion and debate. Through these summits, we collaborate and improve on areas such as the token issuer admission process, or redefining the listing and Sponsor rules.   4. Infinitus Token Sale Concluded  Congratulations to the team at Infinitus for selling 92.89% of their tokens! It’s great to see innovative projects get the funding they need to provide solutions through the blockchain. You can find out more about the Infinitus project here:  https://infinitustoken.io/    5. Token Sales Live on the GRID  Just a reminder, we have two token sales on the GBX-GRID. Both the Õpet and the Crowdvilla sales are currently live, and you can view the details here:  https://grid.gbx.gi/?utm_source=telegram&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=ceomessage      Here is a quick snapshot of the projects:  Crowdvilla is a community-focused, blockchain, non-profit organisation that provides a platform for users to share holiday homes around the world.  https://gbx.gi/crowdvilla-faq/?utm_source=telegram&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=ceomessage    Õpet is a foundation project building a blockchain to store the educational admission data of all students. In order to ensure data is accurately collected at the source, Õpet is also developing a mobile application chatbot to expand students' horizons.  https://gbx.gi/opet-faq/?utm_source=telegram&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=ceomessage  6. Referral Programme  We are still working behind the scenes, making sure that when we roll out our referral programme, it rewards ROCK token holders for helping to grow and expand our amazing community. It is our way of saying thank you for all the support and encouragement. We want it to be perfect! We’ll be announcing its roll-out shortly, so keep a look out!  7. The GBX-DAX App  The GBX-DAX app is now available for all Android users. Our new App will give our users mobility and the freedom to trade from their phones anytime, anywhere. Managing your DAX portfolio, or making trades, will now be even more accessible than ever before.  https://gbx.gi/dax-mobile-app/?utm_source=telegram&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=ceomessage  8. Trading Fees now in effect  As part of our DAX upgrade this week, our new trading fee structure is now in effect. It’s more great news for RKT holders, as you can now reduce your trading fees by holding 10,000 RKT in your account. You can find the full information regarding the DAX trading fees in the link below:  https://exchange.gbx.gi/v1/common/allAccessFile/readForAll?fileUrl=46  That’s all for the moment. Lots of exciting things coming out very soon as I head back to Gibraltar to continue our work on the GSX Group ecosystem. I’m sure you have many questions, and the team here will be on hand to help.    Keep on ROCKing everyone!  Nick Cowan CEO - GSX Group

Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Hi monarx911, are you aware that RKT is a utility token? The plans for the token are outlined in the following post: (a) settling of the GBX application fee ("Application Fee"), listing fees (“Listing Fees”) and Sponsor fees (“Sponsor Fees”) on GBX; (b) staking by Sponsors on GBX (has been removed); (c) settling trading fees (“Trading Fees”) on the GBX Market; (d) medium to pay fees in the GBX Ecosystem including corporate services, fund services, business solutions and e-money services; (e) GBX Blockchain Innovation Centre campaigns, rewards for GBX Blockchain Innovation Centre campaigns and other incentives.  It is also planned to provide: (f) membership to GBX, with privileged account benefits including potential discounts; (g) priority access to token sales; and (h) other potential incentives and voting rights on select community initiatives and developments;  We also have a video explaining all utility use cases: https://youtu.be/aRmzmH04H20

Author: TheCraMan
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Dear ROCKers,  On 19th September 2018 at 03:00 UTC, the GBX-DAX will be undergoing a planned upgrade.  The upgrade process will take less than 24 hours, though we will make the system online as soon as the upgrade is completed.   These regular scheduled upgrades are to continue the development and improvement of the exchange and are an integral part of our system maintenance.   This upgrade will include:   * Optimising our sign up process for both Personal and Corporate accounts to make the user experience much more clear and user friendly.   * DAX System Upgrade / what is being updated?  - API 2.0 - We’re releasing a brand new version of our API in this upgrade, which includes REST and Websocket. This will come complete with documentation and user support.  The new API keys will be available to all users holding a minimum balance of US$1,000 in digital assets.  - Transaction Hash - All our DAX users will be able to find their transaction hash of withdrawals in their account going forward.  - Fiat pair decimals - We’re adding additional decimal places to all our fiat pairs.   * Mobile App will be live as soon as the GBX-DAX system upgrade is complete.   You will then be able to find the app on the Google Play Store.  The Apple iOS version is coming soon and we will keep you all updated as soon as it’s released.   * Zero-Fee trading period is coming to an end after the upgrade, however the integration for our GBX FORT Referral Rewards programme will soon be taking place.  This is the starting point for our incredible referral programme that will be going live soon.  RKT holders will also be able to enjoy discounts off the standard trading fees.  Keep your eyes peeled for more information coming soon.   Thanks for your continued support and remember, keep on ROCKing!   The Team  GBX

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 07/09/18  Since I wrote to you last, we have witnessed significant volatility in the markets and, with it, some voices of concerns about where the token industry is heading.  We ignore the naysayers and, regardless of market conditions, look to the future with increasing confidence. There are a number of reasons why, that I‘d like to share with you.   The demand for higher standards is now greater than ever before and comes from every corner: governments, regulators, industry, and general consumers. As a result standards, accountability and transparency are improving.  There is of course still work to do on a global level but players such as GBX, in supportive jurisdictions like Gibraltar, continue to take bold steps to help move the industry forward, to increase confidence. The GBX-GRID (token sale platform) and our GBX-DAX (Digital Asset Exchange) are venues where today token issuers, buyers, and sellers can go and be treated honestly and fairly.   Furthermore, the emergence of security tokens (securities issued in token form onto blockchains) are the beginning of the next evolutionary step for our industry: to create new products, new markets, widen participation and liquidity, enhance the delivery of service in capital markets, and improve the risk profile of the market’s infrastructure.   From our meetings with many people in the industry, including more recently at conferences in London and Singapore, we believe that many are overwhelmed with information on this subject but at the same time, hungry for knowledge and eager for a regulatory compliant solution.   Just as we are doing for utility tokens, we at GBX are playing a significant role in providing global leadership on security tokens within the GSX Group. Providing clarity, consistency and certainty on this matter is truly one of the main themes to watch out for now and into 2019. We are eager to share with you our plans soon and we wish for all our ROCKers to join us on this important step in our journey.  In the meantime I have some fantastic updates to share, including some great upcoming announcements, so let's get to it ROCKers!   Welcoming CCMC to the Sponsor Firm Network  Our global network continues to grow, strengthening our offering for the GBX. Their experience as blockchain venture capital investors brings additional strength to the network.  It’s a pleasure to welcome Martin and the CMCC team to the GBX.  https://gbx.gi/news/cmcc-global-joins-the-gbx-sponsor-firm-community/?utm_source=telegram   New GBX-DAX Listings  Very soon we will be announcing new additions to our exchange, the GBX-DAX. Since launch, the feedback on the exchange has been great, but we know that you would like to see more developments so the team has been working hard on this. We can’t wait to share this with you, and we’re sure you won’t be disappointed when we do.   https://exchange.gbx.gi/?utm_source=telegram  CGRID Sold Out On GBX-GRID  Another success story for the GBX-GRID (our token sale platform) was the completed sell out of CGRID in the first hour of their Early Access period. The phenomenal timing is another example of one of the prime benefits those holding RKT receive: that first mover advantage. Congratulations to the Carbon Grid team for their successful token raise! To find out more about their project and the sale, click the link below:  https://gbx.gi/news/cgrid-token-sold-gbx-grid/?utm_source=telegram   Infinitus, Õpet & Crowdvilla sales are currently live  I wanted to remind you all that you can find the current live token sales on the GBX-GRID. Here’s a quick snapshot of what’s currently live:  Infinitus is a project that enables users to store encrypted digital data, including private keys, recovery seeds, passwords, pin codes or any alphanumeric data, as a decentralised app (dAPP). https://gbx.gi/inf-faq/?utm_source=telegram  Crowdvilla is a community-focused, blockchain, non-profit organisation that provides a platform for users to share holiday homes around the world. https://gbx.gi/crowdvilla-faq/?utm_source=telegram  Õpet is a foundation project building a blockchain to store the educational admission data of all students. In order to ensure data is accurately collected at the source, Õpet is also developing a mobile application chatbot to expand students' horizon. https://gbx.gi/opet-faq/?utm_source=telegram   Events Roundup  Our Business Development team have been on the road again. Visiting three consecutive events over the course of a week. GBX was invited to speak at Singapore Blockchain Summit, the Blockchain Invasion and the Insider’s Edition. You can catch up on their mini-events tour here:  https://gbx.gi/news/gbx-blockchain-summit-singapore-blockchain-invasion-insiders-edition/?utm_source=telegram     The GBX DAX App is so close  Within the next two weeks, we will be are unleashing the power of the DAX in your pocket. Our new mobile App gives our users the ability to trade on the go, check their portfolios and manage their digital assets effortlessly. The App doesn’t compromise, with professional trading tools, comprehensive portfolio tracking, instant order placement and seamless fiat onboarding. It will be available on Google Play and the Apple App Store soon.  Heading to Asia next week  I’ll be travelling  to Asia next week, with the team to attend Cryptocurrencies & Digital Assets Dialogue in Vietnam on the 15th - 16th September, followed by our Sponsor Firm meetup and Consensus Singapore on 19th & 20th September. It’s looking like a packed out schedule as we continue our work across the globe. If you’re attending either of these events, let us know, it’s always great to meet the FORT community members.  https://www.vietnamcryptodialogue.com/ https://www.coindesk.com/events/consensus-singapore-2018/  GSX Group Joins The FIX Trading Community  GSX Group has become a member of the FIX Trading Community, which includes some of the world’s largest financial institutions. Only through collaboration can we achieve the highest standards, and this membership is a great step in our continued motivation to maintain our industry leading standards. You can find out more about this partnership here:  https://gbx.gi/news/the-gsx-group-joins-the-fix-trading-community/?utm_source=telegram     Our referral program is coming soon for all FORTs  Soon enough, all our FORTs will be able to participate in our referral programme. We want to say thank you for being an integral part of our ecosystem and as such we’re trying to create the best referral program we can. We’ll be announcing more details and the documentation very soon, so keep an eye out for that.   That’s it for today, as always remember the team are here to answer any questions and we will continue to share all the latest news as it happens.  Keep on ROCKing everyone!  Nick Cowan CEO - GSX Group

Author: TheCraMan
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 24/08/18  Hi ROCKers,  It’s been another busy two weeks as we approach the end of the summer season. In Gibraltar and Asia, the teams have been hard at work as always and the new HQ is becoming a hive of activity as the business comes together under one roof. I would like to share with you some of great work and the progress the team at GBX have made in the last two weeks.     1. Blockchain Assets Capital become the 19th Sponsor Firm  We welcome the boutique investment and advisory firm Blockchain Assets Capital (BAC), based in Australia, to our Sponsor Firm network. The continual growth of our global network shows the continued belief in the GBX Ecosystem. With more firms around the world onboard we will continue to see top quality token sales be presented to the GRID. I’m thrilled to welcome the team onboard and can’t wait to see what they bring to the GRID. To find out more about BAC, see the link below:  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/blockchain-assets-capital-approved-to-become-gbx-sponsor-firm-ef3ae48dd2d2  2. Iconiq Bring ICNQ Token To The GBX GRID.  The Iconiq team, one of our Sponsor Firms, have been hard at work developing their own digital asset management project as part of Iconiq Holdings. It’s fantastic to see our Sponsor Firms wanting to use the GBX GRID for their own projects. Their token - ICNQ -  is being adapted to work within their growing ecosystem. Exciting times all round and if you want to find out more, see the link below:  https://gbx.gi/news/iconiq-holding-launch-icnq-token-gbx-grid/  3. Infinitus Token Sale Is Now Live  The Infinitus project token sale is now live. Infinitus is an encrypted storage Dapp of digital data. Their token sale of INF is currently taking place on the GBX GRID. The project was brought to the GBX GRID by Sponsor Firm Venture Capital Network. We wish them the best of luck. For more information about the sale and the project, click on the link below:  https://gbx.gi/news/infinitus-token-sale-announcement/   4. BIC & Blockchain: Back To Basics  The GSX Group Blockchain Innovation Centre and Digital Asset Management (DAM) co-hosted a meetup at the Sunborn Hotel in Gibraltar. The event was titled Blockchain: Back To Basics and was designed to support the growing blockchain economy here on The Rock. The Meetup was a huge success with over 100 people in attendance from firms offering support services for the DLT and blockchain industry in Gibraltar. It’s been great to see the positive feedback from the event and we’ll be hosting more educational meetups and workshops going forward. You can watch a news report from Gibraltar’s local broadcaster GBC on the event here:  https://www.gbc.gi/news/back-basics-educational-meetup-explains-crypto-evolution  5. The GBX DAX Grows  The GBX Digital Asset Exchange is growing from strength to strength with the number of registered users increasing each week. Originally we had planned to have zero fee trading for all those that registered before the 17th August, now we’re pleased to announce that we have extended this to the 14th September. If you haven’t signed up yet, don’t miss out!   6. Rock Meetup in Singapore  The GBX team in Asia held their second ROCKout meetup in singapore, these monthly events are an opportunity for the community to come together to learn and network. This month’s meetup was focused on the blockchain ecosystem and the key stakeholders involved. An enthusiastic crowd of more than 100 people turned up. Another great event showing the engagement from our FORTs across the globe. To find out more about the event, click below:  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-monthly-rockout-meet-up-aug-2018-3aa1a514fec5  7. Referral program coming soon     I’m excited to announce that we will be rolling out our innovative referral program soon. This will be open to all FORTS of the GBX and will allow you to earn rewards for supporting and encouraging our continued growth. You can find your referral code under your profile once logged in to the GBX, we’ll let you know as soon as it’s live and ready to be shared. Our FORT (Friends of Rock Tokens) community has always been one of the most supportive out there and now this is another effort to show our thanks. Keep an eye out for more details soon.   - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  It’s a pleasure as always to give these updates and our continued development relies on you as a community as much as does with us. Keep giving us your feedback, keep asking us questions and most importantly…  Keep on ROCKing!  Nick Cowan CEO - GBX

Author: paskal_navi
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 10/08/18   Hi ROCKers,  It’s the summer season which means, for many of our Community, the holiday season. While Europe has been engrossed with an unprecedented heatwave, here at the GBX we’ve been hard at work. Let’s kick off with the news.  As you are aware, the GBX Digital Asset Exchange is now live and open to the public. In our first two weeks we have been really pleased with the account opening procedures, deposit and withdrawal processes as well as the feedback from the community.  On the back of that significant milestone, I am thrilled to share further developments over the last couple of weeks.  1. New tokens on the GBX GRID As you may have seen, the GRID is filling up fast:  The Õpet Foundation’s token issuance has been admitted to launch on the GBX. The Õpet token, OPET, will be available for sale, supported by Sponsor Firm Venture Capital Network (VCN).  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/%C3%B5pet-admitted-to-the-gbx-grid-38e14cef2e45  The Singapore-based Sponsor Firm Venture Capital Network (VCN) has successfully submitted a new token issuer, Infinitus, and their token INF to the GBX GRID. For more information about the Infinitus Project, please visit:  https://gbx.gi/news/infinitus-token-sale-admitted-for-launch-on-gbx-grid/  Crowdvilla announced the start of the their token sale on the 6th August on the GRID. The initial Early Access Pre-Sale phase ends on August 31 with 30% bonus. There is a 14 day cooling off period before the contribution can be made, so make sure you register your interest before the 16th August to take advantage of the early access bonus. You can find more information here:  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/crowdvilla-token-sale-announcement-4e7e29c8c4ab  2. The Sponsor Firm Community Grows The Sponsor Firm network has gained a Gibraltar and UK based addition to the continually growing community. Ramparts have been approved to become the 18th Sponsor Firm offering more opportunities for token issuers to launch from the GBX-GRID. You can find out more here:  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/ramparts-approved-as-gbx-sponsor-firm-16fbe2d0ac30  3. T2T Lists On The Digital Asset Exchange (DAX) After Traceto.io had their successful token sale on the GBX GRID, the T2T token is now listed on the GBX Digital Asset Exchange. T2T faced tough market conditions, but this is a company that has a great product (which we use) and the utility the token provides will only grow. T2T will be the first of many tokens launched from the GBX GRID that are then available to participants through our exchange.  You can register to trade on the GBX Digital Asset Exchange here:  https://platform.gbx.gi/register  4. Remember, Zero Trading Fees till the 14th September. I just want to remind everyone, if you haven’t already signed up, you have one week left to make sure you benefit from Zero Trading Fees on the Digital Asset Exchange until the 14th September. Remember the cut off date is the 17th August.  5. The GBX Plan I have set the management team of GBX a number of objectives over the next 6 months:  to increase the amount of tokens on the Grid To grow the number of secondary tokens trading on the DAX To grow the Sponsor network To grow the User base To increase liquidity on the DAX  Below I list some of the initiatives we currently have or are implementing.  a) Early Access  For the GBX GRID, RKT plays an integral role, for both Sponsor Firm fees and Issuer staking. It also allows holders (with 10,000 RKT or more) to gain early access to the new token sales on the platform. But that’s not all.  b) Reduced Trading Fees  Both individuals and corporate account holders can reduce their trading fees by holding RKT. If you’re holding enough RKT, you can reduce your fees further, with discounted rates starting when you hold just 10,000 RKT in your account, all the way down to ZERO fees if you hold an amount of RKT we will announce shortly.  c) Native mobile apps launching shortly  The mobile app for both Android and iOS is currently under development and reaching its final stages of testing. Once it's ready you won't be disappointed.  d) The GBX Referral Programme  Soon we shall be announcing an exciting referral programme for the GBX Digital Asset Exchange. This will be a way for us to continue to grow and reward our community of GBX DAX users and RKT holders, and we can't wait to share more details with you as soon as possible!  e) Secondary Tokens  We have been working closely with our Sponsors to onboard secondary tokens - let me say we have some incredible secondary tokens lined up to list on GBX DAX (hint, they are world-famous and you have probably heard of all of them!)  f) Adding more deposit channels  We will grow our banking network and payment providers over the next few months and we will also add additional fiat currencies to the DAX over the next few weeks.  g) Continual upgrades of our trading platform to be expected  We have received lots of useful feedback from you regarding the DAX, and we are reviewing it all. We are also building some great institutional relationships for the DAX, we are unable to disclose any information at this time. We are looking at improving our API and have an upgraded release coming soon. We have our list and we will work hard to deliver a great platform and great trading products, so stay tuned for that in the next few weeks  h) Marketing  After the recent announcement of our new Chief Operating Officer, Phil Walker coming on board, I mentioned a little while ago that we would be rolling out user acquisition and retention marketing strategies, based on the most optimal campaigns used by the online gaming industry. The GBX Marketing Committee is working hard on the plan and we will see this being rolled out over the next few months, but I am really excited about what the team have produced so far.  Round Up  Meanwhile, not only are we are hard at work on GBX - we are also burning the candle at both ends, to deliver the GSX Tokenised Securities Exchange plan - it is going to be truly game changing. And RKT will be key to this platform…..but that’s for another day.  There’s still plenty of work to be done, but I am so proud of what the team has achieved to date and look forward to sharing the journey with you as we continue to move forward, building the entire GSX Group Ecosystem. I have always tried to hire people smarter than me and then empower them to make a difference. With this team I have outdone myself! Our team is the best!! They are smart, they work hard and they push the boundaries of what is possible. It’s everything I look for.  Embrace risk - don’t be afraid of failure - get on with it! Have fun. Our values:  Integrity - Respect - Reputation.  Remember, the ROCK token is the fuel for the entire GSX Ecosystem!  Keep on ROCKing!  Nick Cowan CEO - GBX

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 27/07/18  Dear ROCKers,  It has been a very busy and very productive two weeks for the entire team here at GBX and I’m excited to share this update with you:   1. The GBX Digital Asset Exchange Is LIVE.  The 23rd of July marked one of the most important days for GBX as a business. The GBX Digital Asset Exchange is open to the public. After going through the KYC process, individuals and institutions will be able to trade Bitcoin, Ethereum, and our own Rock Token (RKT) with the US Dollar. We have opened with fiat onboarding making it easier for our users to get started on our institutional-grade platform. Additionally, against BTC and ETH, there are other crypto pairs that you can trade including BCH, ETC and LTC.  This launch is the biggest milestone for the GBX so far and one that has taken countless hours of incredible work from the team, demonstrating how much we can achieve together. Not forgetting the amazing support from our community, and as a thank you, we have launched with zero trading fees until the 14th September 2018, as long as you are signed up by the 17th August 2018! Don’t miss out.   Details of our exclusive trading competition will be announced soon, so stay tuned ROCKers!  For more information on this incredible milestone, visit:  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/the-gbx-digital-asset-exchange-is-now-open-to-the-public-36b945c2fddf   2. DLT Capital, Stratx & MasterNode Ventures Become Sponsor Firms  Our Sponsor Firm network continues to grow, and we are happy to announce that there are three new additions to the network since my last update. Let’s give a warm welcome to DLT Capital, Stratx and Masternode Ventures.  Based in Germany, DLT Capital is an international consultancy and investment firm, comprising of industry experts with extensive experience in traditional corporate finance, coupled with community and marketing management services.  You can find out more about DLT Capital here: https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/dlt-capital-joins-the-gbx-sponsor-firm-network-823db93c4e02    Stratx Consulting Inc specialises in due diligence and research relating to crypto-assets. The team behind Stratx, based in Toronto, Canada, have a great deal of experience in blockchain and traditional capital markets, giving a well-rounded and comprehensive service to token issuers.  You can find out more about Stratx here: https://medium.com/@stratx/stratx-officially-announced-as-gbx-sponsor-firm-a62e3fd9f4b4   MasterNode Ventures is an Australian based blockchain/cryptocurrency advisory service and incubator, founded in December 2017 after conducting one of Australia’s most successful token sales to date.  You can find out more about MasterNode Ventures here: https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/masternode-ventures-a-new-addition-to-the-sponsor-firm-network-593dccd9b094  3. Zero Carbon Project Admitted To The GRID  The Zero Carbon Project has been admitted and is now getting ready for it’s token sale on the GBX GRID, with a start date to be announced soon. The project aims to offer a marketplace to help reduce carbon emissions and is the first token sale brought to the Grid by Sponsor Firm AmaZix, who have considerable experience in the crypto and blockchain space.  For more information about the Zero Carbon Project please see the GRID: https://grid.gbx.gi/  4. On The Road As Always  It was back to back events for our team in Singapore last week as they attended the World Blockchain Conference and World Blockchain Summit, participating in 3 panels and as a judge for some ICO pitches.  To finish off the successful events the team hosted the inaugural GBX FORT (Friends Of ROCK Token) Monthly Rockout Meetup. Keep an eye out for more news on future Meetups as we’ll be taking this on the road across the globe over the coming months.  You can read all about the week in Singapore here: https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-at-world-blockchain-conference-world-blockchain-summit-and-the-inaugural-gbx-fort-monthly-251ff3330dc2  That’s it from me, onwards and upwards as the saying goes. We’ve had an incredible 2 weeks, but there is still so much we want to do. As you all know the Exchange is live and we’re loving the feedback the community is giving us so far. Don’t stop as each piece of feedback helps us to continue the development of both the GRID and the Digital Asset Exchange.  I’m signing off for now and remember, keep on ROCKing everyone!  Nick Cowan CEO - GBX

Body: Hey ROCKers!  It’s here, the day you’ve all been waiting for… The GBX Digital Asset Exchange is now live and open to the public.  This is possibly the most important update I’ve ever had the pleasure of giving to the community. After months of hard work from all the team we’ve finally made it. The platform is now live and ready for you to use.  We’re launching the exchange with the following cryptocurrencies; RKT, BTC, ETH, LTC, BCH and ETC.  That’s not all…  Today I’m also thrilled to let you all know that we have FIAT onboarding available to all our users, starting right now. That means you can now trade the following pairs; RKT/USD, BTC/USD and ETH/USD.  This is huge news for us and we’re so excited to be sharing this journey with all the FORTs (Friends Of Rock Token) out there.  To say thanks to everyone for your patience and to all those newcomers, we’ve also announced a Zero-Trading Fee period. If you’re already signed up, or if you sign up before the 17th August 2018, you’ll benefit from a Zero-Trading Fee period, from now until the 14th September 2018.  Here’s a link to the full announcement:   https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/the-gbx-digital-asset-exchange-is-now-open-to-the-public-36b945c2fddf  Remember, keep on ROCKing everybody!  Nick Cowan CEO - GBX

Author: piggyfrog
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 13/07/18   Hey ROCKers,  Mid-July already?!?! They say time flies when you’re having fun. We’ve been working hard across the board, and there is so much going on behind the scenes, it’s incredible! As per usual, here’s my quick update for everyone.  1. Live AMA  On Wednesday 11th July I hosted my first LIVE AMA from the brand new offices in Gibraltar. I strongly urge you all to head over to facebook to watch the video. Our community is always great at getting involved and joining the conversation, so it was great to give you all an update.  https://www.facebook.com/GibBlockEx/videos/2053300811602616/  2. CGRID & CrowdVilla on the GBX GRID  It’s been busy for the GBX GRID recently. We’ve had two new tokens admitted to the GRID and things are ramping up. I know you all want to see more tokens make it to the GRID and it’s something that everyone is working towards. Our Sponsor Firm network continues to grow and as the network grows, the experience and reach across the globe is evident to see. More details about the upcoming sales will be announced as soon as we can, but in the meantime, you can find more details about each of the projects below.  Find out more about CGRID here - https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/carbon-grid-protocol-token-sale-on-the-gbx-grid-the-gibraltar-blockchain-exchange-gbx-has-cfef138bee6e  FInd out more about CrowdVilla here - https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/crowdvilla-token-approved-for-launch-on-gbx-grid-b1bb42d82d4e  3. Sponsor Firm network reaches Australia  Last week we were especially excited to announce that Crypto SA had been approved to join the Sponsor Firm network. Our reach now is more global than ever with 14 Sponsors now confirmed, with further announcements coming very soon. We can boast having Sponsors in North America, UK, Continental Europe, Asia and now Australia. Crypto SA bring with them a wealth of knowledge and experience in the space and of course opens the GRID up to new and exciting projects from “down under”. Welcome to the family gents, we can’t wait to see what you bring to the GRID.  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/crypto-sa-approved-as-first-australian-gbx-sponsor-firm-8bf2c8b032ae  4. New team members  As always, it’s exciting times as we can introduce more new members of our team. Our new Head of Business Development in Gibraltar, Kurt Looyens joins the GSX Group, bringing with him a wealth of experience from a career in institutional banking.  Marta Stejter also joined the team this week as our new Marketing & Events Executive. Her experience in event management, media and communications will be an asset as she becomes a core part of our international marketing team.  We want to welcome them to the team.  Don|GBX admin, [13 лип. 2018 p., 15:59:50]: 5. On the road, as always  This week the team have been hard at work across the globe, pushing the GSX Group and the GBX brand specifically. It’s important to understand that from our point of view we want to continually be sharing the Gibraltar story, not just about GSX/GBX, but as a DLT, blockchain and Fintech friendly jurisdiction at the cutting edge of regulations.  London Fintech Week  Philip Young was invited to address attendees on the “blockchain day” this wednesday, talking about the evolution of token sales. The event has seen a wide range of speakers and panels, ranging from the UK Regulator, the FCA, to the Bank of England talking about innovation within the space. A great event that with more than 2,000 people in attendance. A big thank you to the organisers.  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-at-london-fintech-week-conference-d4bb92d465dc  RISE, Hong Kong  David Wang and Thomas Chao attended RISE conference in Hong Kong this past week. As one of the biggest fintech conferences in Asia, it’s a landmark event for industry. The interest in Gibraltar as a jurisdiction is growing globally, and we are always being asked about how the jurisdiction and the GBX can help projects.  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-at-the-rise-conference-in-hong-kong-eb4502456ea1  6. Keep your eyes peeled  We have a lot of exciting news to share with you in the coming weeks. As always, the team are working tirelessly on developing and building everything behind the scenes. I’m really excited about what’s coming up and again, I urge you to check out my AMA to find out more. I know Don and the team here on TG have been saying bear with us, trust me when I say, it will be worth the wait!  Keep on ROCKing everybody.  Nick Cowan CEO - GBX

Author: James19_402
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 29/06/18  Dear ROCKers  Once again it’s been a busy 2 weeks with the team working hard on all sides. Here’s an update for you on what’s been going on and what’s coming up:  1) Razlin approved as the latest Sponsor Firm.  It’s a great pleasure to welcome Razlin to the Sponsor Firm network. Their experience in emerging markets and investment advisory will continue to help us bridge the gap between traditional and new finance options for companies. Razlin, based in London, is our thirteenth SF to join the network. We’re all looking forward to see what they bring to the GRID.  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/razlin-joins-the-sponsor-firm-network-26f9d34a863a  2) Always on the road.  Over the last 2 weeks the team have been back out on the road, attending events and sharing the latest updates on the GSX Group’s journey to date. The first of these events was in Warsaw, Poland, where Philip Young, Marketing and Business Development Director was invited to speak at the Europe Blockchain Summit.  Find out more here:  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-at-the-europe-blockchain-summit-warsaw-53ceeded2bf1  Targ Patience, GSX Group’s Chief Compliance Officer, was invited to take part in a panel discussion at the RegTech Summit Europe in London. The panel titled “Achieving MiFID II Compliance” saw Targ discussing these issues with representatives from Standard Chartered Bank, BNY Mellon and Grant Thornton LLP.  Find out more here:  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-at-the-regtech-summit-europe-london-2a8fd3da1b59  The team have also just come back from the Blockchain Global Expo in Amsterdam. The 2 day expo saw a lot of interest, not only for the GSX Group, but also Gibraltar as a jurisdiction. Daniel Evans, Senior Manager for Group Development and Strategy presented on the “Evolution of Token Sales” on the first day.  Find out more here:  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-at-the-blockchain-expo-europe-amsterdam-e839e58038a7  3) It doesn’t stop there.  Next week we are in Gibraltar, as the GSX Group Blockchain Innovation Centre brings together the first Partnership meeting. It’s fantastic to be bringing together both local and international partners who want to help develop the jurisdiction as a whole through education and community.  www.bic.gi  The following week the team are back in London for Fintech Week. From the 9th to the 12th July, you can come down to the QEII centre in London and meet the team. Philip Young has been invited to deliver a keynote on Wednesday, so be sure to let us know if you will be attending.  https://www.fintechweek.com  4) Traceto.io token sale fully sold! 100%! We thank you all for the support!  The first token sale on the GBX GRID has come to an end earlier than anticipated. It’s been an incredible journey for the Traceto.io team and we’re so happy to see how well they have done, selling out their public sale in what has been a challenging environment. Well done!  I caught up with Chye Kit, CEO from Traceto.io earlier this week for a quick video call. Watch the video here:  https://youtu.be/chA0yLhxITw  5) The GBX GRID  We have a new listing approved! The Carbon Grid Protocol (CGRID) aims to raise awareness, accelerate adoption, and revive the carbon credit market globally. CGRID’s ambition is to be the digital gateway to a carbon neutral world, creating a trusted effective mechanism to combat climate change, More details of the sale will be available next week and their official announcement is coming very soon.  6) The Digital Asset Exchange  I know you’re all eager to find out what’s been going on, so here’s a quick update. The Soft Launch has been great. It’s been fantastic to have our platform in the hands of the real people who are going to be using it going forward. The feedback has been great so far and we have so many possible new features from you our community, that we’ll be working hard to decide how to roll these out.  If you didn’t make it to the soft launch, don’t worry. I’ll have good news for you soon and I’m sure you won’t be disappointed.  7) Lastly, we are planning to host a special AMA from our new offices in Gibraltar very soon! Please keep your eyes peeled in our TG channel for the date, but in the meantime, feel free to send in your questions now.  Remember everyone, keep on ROCKing!  Nick Cowan  CEO - GSX Group

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 15/06/18  Dear ROCKers  The last two weeks have, yet again, provided me with much to report and reflect upon:  1. The Digital Asset Exchange Soft Launch The soft launch is now underway and 300 retail and institutional participants are now online using the Exchange. It’s just the beginning and the feedback has been great so far. So many innovative ideas and new developments for us to process and consider. The soft launch will be running for about another 2 weeks and we encourage you to collect your feedback and get in touch. For those of you that have provided us with comments and feedback, thank you so much. Your input is really important to us and will help us to keep developing the exchange with what you want.  2. Two new Sponsor Firms joined the network It’s a pleasure to welcome Lightbulb Capital to our Sponsor Firm network. Based in SIngapore and Hong Kong, their knowledge and experience continues to grow the Sponsor Firm network in Asia. Matthew and Dan focus on creating long-term sustainable businesses helping token issuers throughout the entire token sale process. https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/new-sponsor-firm-lightbulb-capital-digital-40f65cbc4847 Pegasus Fintech have been approved as the first North American Sponsor Firm. With decades of experience, the team at Pegasus supports the growth of token issuers’ businesses. As our 12th Sponsor to join the network it’s clear to see the talent joining the team and opening up a whole new region. https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/pegasus-fintech-approved-as-first-north-american-gbx-sponsor-firm-5c501a5639ca  3. It’s been another busy two weeks for events Last week I was invited to speak at the European Commerce Registers Forum (ECRF). It  was an interesting event to see how technology, specifically blockchain, is having an impact on the sector. https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/european-commerce-registers-forum-gibraltar-d4560e60c67e Philip Young was in Dublin earlier this week for Money Conf. Another big name conference from the Web Summit team. https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-at-moneyconf-event-dublin-ireland-edfee10dac0b I joined the team at the Startup Grind Europe conference in the Central Hall in Westminster, London. We hosted a breakout session panel titled, “Gibraltar: The Crypto Harbour for Fintech and Blockchain” alongside Paul Astengo, Senior Executive Gibraltar Finance and Co-Chair of the DLT Working Group and George Mcdonaugh, CEO of KR1. https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-at-startup-grind-europe-london-6522d50e5cc6  4. Still out on the road The next two weeks seem just as busy for the team. We have some events coming up and we want to make sure you know where we are, hopefully so you can come down and meet the team. On the 21st June we’re in Warsaw, Poland for the BlockchainNext event where Philip Young has been invited to speak. 27-28th June the team will be in Amsterdam for the Global Blockchain Expo event. If you’re attending make sure you let us know and arrange to meet up with the team on location. We’re always happy to meet FORTs from our community. Keep up with all the latest on our events on our website: https://gbx.gi/#events  5. Traceto.io public sale is under way. Just a quick reminder that the Traceto.io public sale is currently underway. The sale is running smoothly, with 89% sold, and if you’re a KYC cleared account holder on the GBX GRID all you need to do is login and you’ll be ready to contribute. For everything you need to know about the T2T sale, check out the link below: https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/everything-you-need-to-know-about-traceto-ios-token-sale-on-the-gbx-grid-updated-cc3ab85392fe  6. STRYKZ Update Unfortunately, as many of you will know, the STRYKZ sale is no longer happening on the GBX GRID. Stryking is a German company and it came to our attention that BaFin (the German financial services regulator) has taken a recent stance in respect of overseas crypto platforms, the long and the short of which means that, in order for there to be certainty in respect of the regulatory position, it is well advised to seek confirmation from BaFin that the token in question is not a regulated financial instrument. It should be pointed out that Stryking acting on its own in its token sale faced no such risks. The advice was therefore that using the GBX Grid to launch their token required this clearance, a process that would have probably taken a few weeks. Although we were confident that Stryking could undertake the necessary steps to achieve this, with Stryking's desire to launch the token sale during the World Cup period which is upon us, it was clear that the timing was not going to work.  The GBX, in agreement with Stryking, therefore elected to withdraw from the token sale to unquestionably ensure adherence to German financial product legislation. While we are disappointed that the STRYKZ token sale will no longer take place on the GBX Grid, we will continue to collaborate with the Stryking team as their exciting project develops.  In a perfect world we would have spotted this before but we didn’t - and no-one else did - it’s tough to be aware of all of the pitfalls without stepping into some of them. Our job at GBX and my job as CEO is to deal with these issues as they emerge - identify the problem, ascertain the risks and make the right decision in the best interests of our stakeholders - Issuers, buyers, sponsors and RKT holders - then put in a process to stop it happening in the future. We spotted the issue - we immediately dealt with it. We learn from this. We move on, stronger. Remember everyone, keep on ROCKing!  Nick Cowan  CEO - GSX Group

Author: piggyfrog
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Hi there. Users will be able to attain major digital assets, such as Bitcoin, Ethereum, Dash, Ripple, and Litecoin that have perceived strong credibility, user base, and liquidity along with tokens listed on GBX’s token sale platform. Different tokens are expected to be incrementally added over time as the token sale platform and digital asset exchange develops.  Thank you for your comment. We agree. While we are not pursuing multiple listings, we cannot, unfortunately, prevent our token from being listed on other exchanges should they wish to. On CMC, with the soft launch of the GBX DAX, we are now providing them with price and volume data. It can only be a matter of time before the correct information is being accurately reflected.  The GBX DAX exchange will be fully-operational after the sofw launch, which will last for 2-3 weeks

Author: Madlen
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: GBX aims to become the world's first licensed and regulated platform for the sale of tokens and digital exchange assets managed by the regulated European Union stock exchange ("EU").  More specifically, gbx-this is expected to be:  a global marketplace for listing and selling tokens that satisfy the strict due diligence process and the admissibility process set out in the "GBX rules"; exchange of high-quality digital assets, including a market in which issuers of tokens, traders and investors can confidently and reliably participate in a platform where the listed tokens have been subjected to an institution-level approval process.

Author: Madlen
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Gbx is expected to be different from other participants in the marker and digital assets; GSX Tokenised is also a security that will provide financial services and a fintech ecosystem that will provide professional services to support the full range of market participants ("ecosystem position").

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: CEO FORTnightly Message - 01/06/18   Hey ROCKers!  I know I say this every week, but once again, I can’t believe two weeks have been and gone already. There is so much going on at the moment and as always our community of FORTs continue to show their incredible support and enthusiasm for the GBX project.  Without further ado, let’s get stuck in to the good stuff.  1. A big welcome to the new additions to the team   We’ve been busy building our team and today it’s a great pleasure to be able to introduce you to the latest team members to join us on our journey. I’m sure you’ll all join me in giving them a warm welcome.  Chief Operating Officer – Phil Walker Before joining GSX, Phil had a long career as global lead within operations and marketing for a major global online gaming group. Latterly he was a Managing Director for Ladbrokes Coral.  Group Chief Compliance Officer – Targ Patience Targ has extensive experience as a senior regulator officer and consultant.  Firms that he has worked with include Citigroup Global Markets, London Clearing House Clearnet, Goldman Sachs and KPMG.  Head of Exchange and Listings Authorisation Team – Daniel Torres Daniel’s international business career has spanned regulated financial, crypto and technology sectors , as well  business start ups. His work has taken him across South America, Africa and Europe and we welcome him to Gibraltar.  Head of Customer Relations  – Dionissis Daoussis Dion’s 15 year career as a customer services team leader and supervisor with some of the world’s leading online gaming businesses, makes him ideally suited to create for us a new paradigm in customer services.  2. Blockchain Worx joins the GBX Sponsor Firm network  The 10th Sponsor Firm to be approved in our Network is Blockchain Worx. It’s a great pleasure to welcome the team from the Singapore based company. They provide a range of ancillary solutions including an Anti-Money Laundering Transaction Monitoring system, a Securities Tokenisation platform and an Enterprise Blockchain Innovation Centre to token issuers. That’s not all, as part of their continued growth they are opening an office in Dubai soon, with more offices in Europe already planned.  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/blockchain-worx-joins-the-sponsor-firm-network-c93c0b9b712c  3. Traceto.io public sale coming soon  There’s so much going on at the moment that I wanted to make sure that none of us forget or miss out on the upcoming public sale of T2T, the Traceto.io token sale. The sale starts on the 8th June, that’s next monday.  If you haven’t already done so, make sure you’ve registered and gone through the KYC process on the GBX Grid so as you can take part in the sale. You can get started here https://platform.gbx.gi/register.  Everything you need to know about the T2T sale can be found here - https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/everything-you-need-to-know-about-traceto-ios-token-sale-on-the-gbx-grid-updated-cc3ab85392fe  4. STRYKZ is the next token sale on the GBX Grid  It’s great to see the GBX Grid coming to life, and it’s only the beginning. STRYKZ is the next token to be approved and make it to the grid. Stryking is tokenising fantasy sports, with Football Stars, it's live flagship fantasy football competition platform, already creating waves within the football community. The team recently picked up 2 awards at pitch events and the team are working hard across the world getting ready for their upcoming sale, which is scheduled to open to the public during the FIFA World Cup.  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/stryking-to-launch-their-strkyz-token-through-the-gbx-grid-473e48a182df  5. GBX Digital Asset Exchange Soft Launch  It’s with huge excitement that today I can tell you that our GBX Digital Asset Exchange will be opening its doors for a soft launch and exclusive early access next week. I know that this is the news we’ve all been waiting for and the whole team has been working around the clock to make this a reality. The Soft Launch will only be available to 300 retail and select institutional participants. The selection process will be simple, the first 100 people to sign up will get guaranteed exclusive early access and then the next 200 will be selected from all other applicants. Please note: You must already be a KYC cleared GBX account holder.  Keep watching this space carefully as we will be sharing the link to register very soon, together with providing further details on the selection process and potential rewards that we’ll be offering successful participants.  6. Our strategic partnership with Quoine  GBX anticipated that it would take more time to develop its own technology – instead we have made significant progress and will roll out our own interface and trading system ahead of schedule, and reinforces our commitment to a strong relationship with Quoine as we see major strategic opportunities working together including: connecting to the deep liquidity offered on the Worldbook/Liquid platform, and offering dual listing opportunities to our issuers and accessing investors in different geographies.  —  We have more news coming early next week so keep an eye out everyone. Things are definitely heating up and the team are doing an incredible job around the clock to keep us moving in the right direction.  Remember everyone, keep on ROCKing!  Nick Cowan CEO - GSX Group

More specifically, gbx-this is expected to be:  a global marketplace for listing and selling tokens that satisfy the strict due diligence process and the admissibility process set out in the "GBX rules"; exchange of high-quality digital assets, including a market in which issuers of tokens, traders and investors can confidently and reliably participate in a platform where the listed tokens have been subjected to an institution-level approval process.

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Nick’s Fortnightly Message to all FORTs (Friends of Rock Token) 18/05/18   Hello ROCKers!  Another two weeks have been and gone, it’s incredible how fast time flies. As always we have been hard at work, not just here in Gibraltar, but on the global stage. There were a few key events I want to focus on in this update.  Sponsor Firm Summit  The GBX held its inaugural Sponsor Firm Summit in Gibraltar on the 09/10th May. It was a fantastic event where our Sponsor Firms from all corners of the globe flew to Gibraltar to come together for a two day event. We kicked off with an amazing sunset reception for 100 at the Rock’s highest wine-bar at 450 mts (which can only be accessed by cable car), where the Hon. Albert Isola, Minister for Commerce - HM Government of Gibraltar, welcomed the sponsor firms to Gibraltar. As well as the Minister, Gibraltar PLC turned out in their masses to give our Sponsors a true Gibraltar welcome including representatives from the banking, accountancy and audit, legal sectors and Gibraltar Finance.  See local TV coverage here:  https://www.gbc.gi/news/gbx-hosts-first-sponsor-firm-summit  Having spent my career in London and Tokyo, it never ceases to amaze me how fortunate we are to work in such an awesome place where we have a Government so committed to supporting the fintech space that they can take time out to welcome our friends. If you haven’t come to Gib…..you MUST!  Day 2 was down to business with an all day training session for the sponsors working through the processes on the GBX Grid, the vetting and listing process, marketing and communication strategies and most importantly, bringing the global network together. It’s great to see our Sponsors explore ways that they can leverage each other’s skills and work together to create a truly epic eco-system that can only help token issuers who choose to use the Grid. I can’t wait for the next Summit where I expect double the number!!  https://gbx.gi/news/gbx-sponsor-summit-gibraltar/  TGV Co-organised Event   The GBX team in Asia co-organised another brilliant event with the team from True Global Ventures (TGV). Dusan and his team produce great events that steer away from the traditional model and create a centre for thought leadership and discussion in the space. David Wang, GBX Executive Director (Asia) participated in a panel; ‘The Past, the Present and the Future of Private Markets.’  https://gbx.gi/news/gbx-co-organises-tgv-event-hong-kong/  Consensus: NYC  If you haven’t heard of Consensus, where have you been this week? it is one of the major events of the year for all things blockchain and crypto. Philip Young, Marketing and Business Development Director for the GBX, (whom some of you have met) flew to New York to attend the event. Phil has been updating us about his trip, you can read more here. https://gbx.gi/news/consensus-day-1%e2%80%8a-%e2%80%8aa-quick-update-new-york-city/  https://gbx.gi/news/day-2%e2%80%8a-%e2%80%8athe-crypto-community-together-manhattan/  Token Summit  In true GBX fashion, there was no time to waste in New York City for Philip Young. Back-to-Back opportunities in the city that never sleeps meant that Phil went straight to Token Summit after Consensus. Luckily for us, Phil is a conference veteran and had more than enough energy to hit the ground running before he jets back home to Europe.  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/token-summit-iii-conference-new-york-city-ef68c835d66b  Techinasia 2018, Singapore  It has been a conference heavy couple of weeks and the GBX has not let up on its push to share our vision with the world. It’s not just about the GBX, but also Gibraltar as a jurisdiction. The interest in Gibraltar as a fintech hub is staggering across the globe. The team in Asia, including Andrew Pal, our Chief Strategy Officer (APAC), made their way to Tech In Asia event, where Executive Director, Ben Soh spoke on a panel about regulation and its effects.   https://gbx.gi/news/gbx-singapore-attending-tech-asia-2018/

Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Traceto.io Token Sale  A reminder to all our ROCKers that the Traceto.io Early Access sale will take place on 21st May (Monday) with an exclusive 5% bonus! Remember, you need to be holding $1000 worth of RKT in order to gain Early Access. You can read more about the sale here on the GBX Grid:  https://grid.gbx.gi/  Also read the FAQ for further details: https://gbx.gi/traceto-faq/  The GBX Trading Exchange  I know this is what you have all been waiting for these last few weeks. The team have been working around the clock, and I’m excited to tell you that we are planning for an important system upgrade during the week beginning 4th of June, subject to the results of our internal testing and development in the next 2 weeks. After the upgrade is done, we will have the soft launch of the Beta version of the GBX Digital Assets Exchange! More details will be available closer to that date. We want to thank you all for your patience and for the continued faith in the project. We’ll be rolling the exchange out in stages in line with our original plans, so keep your eyes peeled for more information.  Keep on ROCKing everybody!  Nick Cowan CEO

Author: James19_402
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Nick’s Fortnightly Message to all FORTs (Friends of Rock Token).  Hey Rockers!   Another busy fortnight – we have had waves of visitors coming to Gibraltar to check out the crypto harbour – ICO issuers interested in joining the Grid, Sponsor candidates, secondary token issuers looking at joining the GBX for trading, tokenised securities issuers keen to know about our plans for GSX later this year and license applicants looking to set up here – it’s so exciting to see the place we call home participating on the crypto global platform within an existing regulatory framework. I have said for a long-time that I see 2018 being the year of the regulator – and my attitude hasn’t changed. Investor protection concerns will drive regulators to continue to take action and in Gibraltar we will see shortly the introduction of token sale regulations as well as enhanced controls for secondary exchanges – all of which we welcome!   Moving on - here’s some of our recent developments that I wanted to share with you in this update:   1. T2T Update We have an update for all those eager to get involved in the Traceto.io token sale, with the details of the sale process and the new date of 21st May 2018 08:15:00 (UTC) for those early access ROCKers! We are excited to get the first GBX Grid token sale underway, you can find out more about the sale here:   https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/everything-you-need-to-know-about-traceto-ios-token-sale-on-the-gbx-grid-updated-cc3ab85392fe   2. VFS Acquisition Juno Services Group, part of the GSX Group, has acquired the Gibraltar based fund administrator Vista Fund Services (VFS). This acquisition builds on our comprehensive service offering and strengthens our ecosystem supporting the crypto industry.   Acquiring VFS further solidifies Juno’s position as the largest fund administrator in Gibraltar, bringing more experienced and dedicated team members into our Group.   You can read about the acquisition here.   https://www.gsx.gi/article/9463/vista-fund-services-acquired-by-gsx-group   3. Sponsor Firm Announcement The GBX Grid is continuing to build our Sponsor Firm network to provide more opportunities for token issuers to get launched and listed through GBX. We have recently announced a wave of new Sponsor Firms including some well-established names in the crypto community all of whom have some interesting projects in the pipeline for launching on the GBX Grid. Our Sponsors have also been paying us Application fees and Approval fees – all of which are paid in RKT – so the utility is now in full use, which is really exciting.   We are now up to nine approved GBX Sponsors all of whom can see the unique benefits of what the GBX Grid provides for Token issuers:   A Mark of Prestige - Only quality tokens make the Grid.  Ready Participants - A Large pool of AML/KYC cleared token sale participants from approved jurisdictions.   Risk Mitigation - Collects contributions from participants and handles the distribution of the tokens thereafter.   Maximum Exposure - Focused attention due to maximum of 9 slots on the Grid.   Value Add - Access to the GSX group ecosystem   Exchange Access - Fast track to listing on the GBX Exchange for secondary trading.   I would like to welcome on board AmaZix, Rockchain and VCN as our latest quality Sponsor Firms.   You can read about these latest Sponsor Firms here: AmaZix https://gbx.gi/news/amazix-joins-gbx-sponsor-firm-network/   Rockchain: https://gbx.gi/news/rockchain-joins-gbx-sponsor-firm-network/   VCN: https://gbx.gi/news/venture-capital-network-joins-gbx-grid-sponsor-firm/   4. Sponsor Firm Summit With the rapid growth of our Sponsor Firm network we are having our inaugural Sponsor Firm Summit in Gibraltar on the 9th & 10th May. This is the first event of its kind and brings together our Sponsors and the GBX team to discuss the operational process of the GBX Grid, as well as plans for the future.   5. KPMG Gibraltar eGaming Summit We were pleased to be invited to speak at the eGaming summit sponsored by KPMG. Our Group CFO, Adrian Hogg spoke on “Commercial Applications for the Blockchain/ Crypto Funds”. I was invited to participate on a panel titled “Gibraltar’s Proposition for FinTech” chaired by Sian Jones from the GFSC. It was a fantastic discussion where we spoke about Gibraltar being a hub for fintech innovation. A big thank-you to KPMG for the invitation!   —- As I mentioned in my last update, the GBX team in Asia continue to work 24/7 on getting our technology ready and I hope to make an important announcement in my next update!! Sit tight and keep the faith.   That’s it for this week. I want to thank you all again for being such an important part of this journey with us. Our team are always available for any questions you may have and I can’t wait to share more with you in the coming weeks.  Remember everyone, keep on ROCKing!  Nick Cowan CEO - GSX Group

Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Hey, no worries. We glad to hear interest. We can explain why do we think GBX will be better then Coinbase, Bitfinex, Binance, Kucoin and all the other exchanges. A couple of factors to bear in mind - firstly we have a very unique proposition given we are a rules based exchange offering a Token Sales Platform and Digital asset exchange with Sponsors with robust rules and secondly the mission of the GBX is to establish a marketplace for utility tokens and cryptocurrencies operating within Gibraltar’s regulatory framework, providing issuers access to a wider community of token buyers, and to create a high standard for entry and a controlled environment with rules for admission and trading, with ongoing obligations and standards of conduct, under the GBX Rules. Please, look at the following video (it might be useful): http://www.gbc.gi/news/gbx-announces-rock-token-sale  The GBX aims to be the world’s first licensed and regulated token sale platform and digital asset exchange, operated by a European Union regulated stock exchange.  Using a sponsor and rules-based system, the GBX will apply to be licensed by the Gibraltar Financial Services Commission (“GFSC”) under the Financial Services (Distributed Ledger Technology Providers) Regulations 2017 (“DLT Regulations”), which came into operation on 1 January 2018 in Gibraltar.  More specifically, GBX is expected to be: (a) a global listing and token sales springboard for utility tokens that have satisfied a strict due diligence process and admission process set out in the “GBX Rules”; and  (b) a high-quality digital asset exchange, including a marketplace where issuers of utility tokens, traders and investors can participate with confidence and trust in a platform where the tokens listed have been subjected to an institutional grade approval process.

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Dear, GBX Community.  Please exercise caution!  Recently the GBX has become the target of interest for scammers on Twitter, offering a free giveaway of Ethereum. Please remember, these are scams. We will never address, offer, solicit our community in public or private messages. We are dealing with these twitter accounts, and so far we have reported and successfully had 14 accounts removed from Twitter. Keep a close eye on not just the Twitter name, OUR OFFICIAL account is @GibBlockEx, but also with when they started posting and what they are posting. Please REPORT @GibB1ocqkkEx This is a FAKE account. Be vigilant, and don't be fooled by these fake accounts.

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: Nick’s Fortnightly Message to all FORTs (Friends of Rock Token). 06/04/2018  Dear ROCKers!  It’s already been two weeks since my last message and so much has been going on. The team have been incredibly busy as always, but I wanted to take this time to give you all an update.  The GBX Grid is now live. [/b] Our Token Launch Centre is now up and running. This is a huge step in the right direction and means we’re ready to ROCK and roll. There is a pipeline of Listing Applications coming in, and we are working hard to review them with the help of our Sponsor Firms.  We’re rolling out new features over the course of this month, but I’m happy to announce that anyone with a verified account can now make deposits to their account, in ETH or in RKT, and we’ll be letting you know soon about BTC deposits too.  As many of you know, the inaugural approved token sale on the GBX Grid, Traceto.io was delayed.  Unfortunate circumstances internally at Traceto.io lead to them taking an executive decision to delay their public sale and to come back at a later date. We have every confidence they are going to come back stronger than ever.  But there’s still so much going on and so much to look forward to.  2. Sponsor Firm Network  Our sponsor firm network is continuing to expand. We have some announcements coming in the next few days about the new SFs that are joining our ecosystem. With new Sponsor Firms will come new token sales and that’s great news for everybody.  These new additions continue to show us, and the world, that Gibraltar is a natural home for this emerging industry.  We’ll be sharing more news about our new SFs very soon.  3. Conferences  The team have been busy once again with events and conferences around the world.  Philip Young and Daniel Evans attended Fintech World Euro Summit London, Blue Chip ICO’s Road Show as the main event sponsors to present the GBX and to take part in a panel about the future of token sales and how standards could be raised in the industry.   https://www.gsx.gi/article/9460/gibraltar-stock-exchange-at-level39-202-fintech-conference  In Asia, it was non-stop as the team took part in Taiwan Blockchain Festival, organised by Blockcity, in Taipei, Taiwan. Ben Soh, Executive Director spoke at the event and the interest in the GBX and Gibraltar was incredible.  https://medium.com/@Gibraltar.Blockchain.Exchange/gbx-team-on-the-panel-at-blockcitys-taiwan-blockchain-festival-58c237c20984  Today, Ben Soh, GBX Executive Director, is speaking at the Singapore Decentralize event. If you’re attending, let us know and make sure you find the team at the event.  https://www.decentralize.sg/#speakers  The GBX team will be heading to London’s Olympia for the Blockchain Expo Global 2018. Philip Young will be speaking on the 2nd day of the event. If you’re attending, keep an eye out for the team and make sure you say hi.   https://blockchain-expo.com/global/  4. Heading to Asia  Later this month I’ll be travelling to Singapore and Japan to continue working with our technology partners QUOINE as we further the development of the GBX Systems. We’re finalising the integration of the GBX Exchange.  I know some of you were asking about the next AMA (Ask Me Anything) and we will be looking at organising one from Japan, so keep your eyes peeled for that.  5. The GSX Group - Blockchain Innovation Centre  We think that building a community requires support from those involved, and to that end we’re ramping up the BIC. The new website is now online (www.bic.gi) and we will be announcing some new events very soon. It’s been so encouraging to see so many people and companies from within the industry in Gibraltar, and internationally, looking to partner with us to develop the community as a whole. It’s going to be a fantastic asset for Gibraltar.  6. Looking to the future  This journey of ours has been moving so fast that sometimes it’s good for us to look back and reflect on just how far we’ve come in such a short space of time. It’s been an incredible journey, but there’s still so much ahead of us.  It really is an exciting time as we grow the GSX Group family, with the development and roll out of new features on the GBX Grid, the upcoming GBX Exchange, new Sponsor Firms coming onboard and our community driven BIC which will be announcing all new educational and community focused events.  The whole team, across the globe, from Gibraltar, Europe and London, through to Hong Kong and Japan, are working hard to keep building the Crypto Harbour to make it the natural home for this emerging industry.  If you have any questions, our community team is here to help. Make sure you’re following us on our online channels so as you don’t miss the latest news and announcements coming soon.  Remember everyone, keep on ROCKing!   Nick Cowan CEO - GSX Group  You can also read the update in our ANN Channel here: https://t.me/GBXannouncements/196

Author: TheCraMan
Title: [ENDED]GBX-The Crypto Harbour.Gibraltar-based Crypto Exchange&Token Platform
Body: we are rolling it out in phases and the token sale  is one of those phases. Please see this message for details of our plans moving forward:   Nick’s Fortnightly Message to all FORTs (Friends of Rock Token).  Hi Rockers,  I have some exciting news for you all.   I’ll be writing a fortnightly newsletter from now on to keep you up to date with all the latest developments from the GSX Group. That includes the Gibraltar Blockchain Exchange, the Gibraltar Stock Exchange, our new company service provider Juno, the Blockchain Innovation Centre in Gibraltar and of course, all things Rock Token!  Yes, it’s a lot of news and everything is moving so quickly at the moment, that’s why it’s so important to me that everyone in our community knows what’s happening.  It’s as busy as ever at the GSX Group offices. We’re preparing the launch of the GBX platform but this hasn’t stopped the team from travelling around the world and attending some incredible events to promote GBX:   1) The GSX BIC partners with Startup Grind Gibraltar, powered by Google for Entrepreneurs  Excited to announce our first formal partnership for the Blockchain Innovation Centre in Gibraltar. The announcement was made at Startup Grind Gibraltar’s 1 year anniversary.   2) Gibraltar Finance and GBX private cocktail receptions in Hong Kong and Singapore  A fantastic welcome in Singapore and Hong Kong in conjunction with Gibraltar Finance and the Hon. Albert Isola, Minister for Commerce.   > Read the full article https://gbx.gi/news/private-cocktail-reception-hong-kong-singapore/  3) GBX invited to be Judge and Co-Organiser of Global Blockchain Competition   What an honour to be asked to be an integral part of the blockchain community on a global scale.   > Read the full article https://gbx.gi/news/gbx-judge-co-organiser-global-blockchain-competition/   4) Cryptocurrency World Expo Berlin  Philip Young, Marketing Director for GBX spoke to the blockchain community in Berlin.    That’s not all.   5) We also attended Money 2020 in Singapore and Token 2049 in Hong Kong.   But that’s just the tip of the iceberg. It’s been a big month in terms of announcements and developments. These are some of our highlights:  6) First sponsor firms announced  Our first three sponsor firms were announced -KR1, Kession and Broctagon - an integral part of the continued development of our ecosystem. We have more applications in the pipeline, with some exciting partnerships to share with you soon.  > Read the full article https://gbx.gi/news/introducing-first-gbx-sponsor-firms/   —-   7) The GBX Grid Token Sale Platform  Our Token Sale platform is almost ready! See it at https://grid.gbx.gi/  We have already published our Token Sale Rules at https://gbx.gi/documents/. They include everything you need to know about our requirements for token launches.  GBX Grid will be rolled out over the next few weeks in a series of releases. Withdrawals have been enabled as many of you will have seen by being able to withdraw RKT.   Deposits will be enabled in less than two weeks time after which Sponsors will be able to upload the relevant information for the Token Sales.   Thus, you will be seeing gradual roll-out of features over the next 4 weeks, so stay tuned as our first batch of Sponsors and Token Sales come online!  The GBX Trading Exchange  As you all know, we have been working hard with Quoine to get our trading technology ready. We expect to roll this out during April.   Our GBX Exchange Rules are ready and have been published today.  In summary  In terms of business, we are extremely optimistic.  We have a healthy number of Sponsors applying, all of whom have a backlog of ICOs. GBX also receives a large number of enquiries daily, which we can now pass on to our Sponsors.   The next few months are sure to be hard work, but the support from our community, sponsors and stakeholders has and continues to be overwhelming.   Remember everyone, keep on ROCKing!   Nick Cowan CEO - GSX Group
